name: rape seed production | rape seed | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/29845/documentation

This inventory represents the production of 1 kg of rape seed in AUS-WAS region. It  has been developed with support from the Australian Commonwealth Government through the National Landcare Programme Innovation Grant and the Grains Research and Development Corporation (GRDC). The inventory was developed by CSIRO, the Department of Primary Industries NSW and Lifecycles. More detail on inventory development can be found in the Methodology for Developing Life Cycle Inventory' documents located at http://auslci.com.au/index.php/AusAgLCI. ;

The inventory includes the processes for growing canola (Rape seed) without irrigation on arable land in Western Australia, Australia. Inputs of fertilisers, pesticides as well as the transports to the farm are considered. All tractor operations, fuel supply and machine infrastructure is included. The direct and indirect emissions on the field from nitrogen application and stubble retention are included. Stubble/straw removed from the field is included in the nitrogen balance but allocation to straw product has been ignored as the fraction of stubble removed on average is low 11%,- and the economic value is generally low. The nitrogen balance also includes leaching of N in different parts of the state based on the ratio of evapouration/ precipitation ratio which results in 30% Nitrogen leaching in 1.5% of the state of WA.  Inventory refers to the production of 1 kg of seeds. Source inventory refers to 1 ha of crop over 1 year, with an average yield value of 1110 kg (dry matter content = 1043.4 kg), from the end of the previous crop to the point of harvesting of the next crop.

The system boundary ends at the field gate with all further processes such as transport, storage, packaging are excluded.
